-- Limited December same-store sales up 4 percent
-- 
-- Thu Jan 4, 2007 7:09am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/04/businesspro-limited-sales-dc-idUSWEN174820070104

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Limited Brands ( LTD.N ) said on Thursday 
its sales at stores open at least a year rose 4 percent in 
December. 

  Analysts, on average, had expected a same-store sales gain 
of 9.3 percent for the five-week period ended December 30, 
according to a Reuters survey.  Total sales for the company, whose store chains include 
Victoria's Secret, Express and Bath & Body Works, rose 6 
percent to $2.03 billion.